data.title: Bhutanese prime minister meets with Aso
data.meta_description: TOKYO, Japan - Japan's Prime Minister Taro Aso (R) holds talks with Bhutan's Prime Minister Jigme Thinley (L) at Aso's office in Tokyo on Sept. 2. (Kyodo)

Memorial Day Of Veteran Nepali Politician BP Koirala Held In Nepal

Nepali Congress President and former Prime Minister Sher Bahadur Deuba (C) is offering garlands on the statue of veteran Nepali politician BP Koirala in Lalitpur, Nepal, on July 21, 2024. (Photo by Subaas Shrestha/NurPhoto)

Memorial Day Of Veteran Nepali Politician BP Koirala Held In Nepal

Nepali Congress President and former Prime Minister Sher Bahadur Deuba is attending a program organized at the Nepali Congress headquarters in Lalitpur, Nepal, on July 21, 2024. (Photo by Subaas Shrestha/NurPhoto)

Politics In India

Supporters of the Trinamool Congress (TMC) party are attending a rally addressed by West Bengal's Chief Minister and party supremo Mamata Banerjee to mark the annual Martyrs' Day in Kolkata, India, on July 21, 2024. (Photo by Sudipta Das/NurPhoto)

Netanyahu Visit Leads To Tight Security At The Watergate Hotel In Washington DC

Washington DC security officials are preparing for Prime Minister Netanyahu's arrival by installing special fences around the Watergate Hotel. Netanyahu is meeting with Biden and the Congress during his visit. (Photo by Andrew Leyden/NurPhoto)
